Funtalk China, Intel, Mosaic, Radian Group: U.S. Equity Movers

-- B y   N i k o l a j   G a m m e l t o f t
-- 
2011-05-31T13:38:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-29/boston-scientific-mosaic-pricesmart-tjx-u-s-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies are
having unusual moves in U.S. trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 9:40 a.m. in  New York .  Funtalk China Holdings Ltd. (FTLK)   jumped 14 percent to
$6.70. The operator of the mainland’s second-biggest chain
selling mobile phones agreed to be bought by Fortress Group
Ltd., a group which includes Arch Digital Holdings Ltd. and GM
Investment Co., for $7.20 a share in a “going private”
transaction.  Intel Corp. (INTC)   rose 1.7 percent to $22.58. The
world’s largest chipmaker is promoting a new type of thinner
laptop called an ultrabook, seeking to help the personal-
computer industry fend off a challenge from Apple Inc.’s iPad
and other tablets.  Mosaic Co. (MOS)   increased 2.1 percent to $71.500.  North
America ’s second-largest fertilizer producer and Potash Corp. of
Saskatchewan Inc. (POT US) were raised to “buy” from “hold”
at Citigroup Inc., which cited a better outlook for the
companies’ earnings. Potash Corp. rose 2.5 percent to $57.36.  Radian Group Inc. (RDN)   gained 8.5 percent to $5.04. The
mortgage insurer was raised to “overweight” from “neutral”
at Piper Jaffray Cos., which cited a stronger position on both
credit and capital.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nikolaj Gammeltoft in New York at 
